    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required levels for MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out per ASME V&V 40 Table 4 for a Class II device at this model risk level. The CFD model demonstrates sufficient credibility to support the COU decision regarding worst-case hemolysis operating conditions. It is noted that the validation dataset does not encompass off-design transient start-up conditions and that edge cases at extreme low-flow operation are not fully covered by the available experimental corpus. This gap is consistent with standard practice for MRL 2 assessments of rotary blood pump CFD models. The overall credibility package is accepted as adequate to support the regulatory submission.",
